  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Response to Fire Emergency in Camps 8 East and 8 West.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to restore lifesaving WASH Infrastructure and services in refugee camps and host communities affected by fire. This UNICEF project 1) repairs and reconstructs piped water networks, handpump water points, inclusive latrines, bathing spaces and faecal sludge management sites and 2) distributes water storage containers, water treatment chemicals, hygiene supplies menstrual hygiene kits. The project provides life-saving assistance to 19,000 people, including approximately 5,000 women, 4,200 men, 10,000 children, and 950 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
